1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,908
Merge Sort is a divide and conquer sorting algorithm.

2
00:00:05,000 --> 00:00:07,348
We start with the complete array.

3
00:00:07,400 --> 00:00:10,204
We divide the array into two halves.

4
00:00:10,266 --> 00:00:14,534
Each half is divided again until we reach single elements.

5
00:00:14,600 --> 00:00:18,436
We now merge elements by comparing and ordering them.

6
00:00:20,533 --> 00:00:26,073
Finally, we merge the two sorted halves to get the final sorted array.

7
00:00:26,133 --> 00:00:31,769
Merge Sort always runs in n log n time and uses extra space.

